#: ../../../arch/arm/swp_emulation.rst:2
msgid "Software emulation of deprecated SWP instruction (CONFIG_SWP_EMULATE)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/arm/swp_emulation.rst:4
msgid ""
"ARMv6 architecture deprecates use of the SWP/SWPB instructions, and "
"recommends moving to the load-locked/store-conditional instructions LDREX "
"and STREX."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/arm/swp_emulation.rst:7
msgid ""
"ARMv7 multiprocessing extensions introduce the ability to disable these "
"instructions, triggering an undefined instruction exception when executed. "
"Trapped instructions are emulated using an LDREX/STREX or LDREXB/STREXB "
"sequence. If a memory access fault (an abort) occurs, a segmentation fault "
"is signalled to the triggering process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/arm/swp_emulation.rst:13
msgid ""
