"of the last process to trigger the emulation to be invocated. For example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/arm/swp_emulation.rst:22
msgid "NOTE:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/arm/swp_emulation.rst:23
msgid ""
"when accessing uncached shared regions, LDREX/STREX rely on an external "
"transaction monitoring block called a global monitor to maintain update "
"atomicity. If your system does not implement a global monitor, this option "
"can cause programs that perform SWP operations to uncached memory to "
"deadlock, as the STREX operation will always fail."
msgstr ""
